Malta, collecting samples for dating. We now have many dates on key localities using OSL and Uranium-series methods. These constrain the ages of the dwarf mammals. Details will be uploaded in due course.

In 2014-16 we have undertaken further fieldwork at Ghar Dalam Cave, Malta and several new localities in Sicily (partly funded by Leverhume Trust but contributing significantly to original NERC grant aims). This has greatly sharpened our understanding of the chronology of these sites and their endemic faunas, Ghar Dalam in particular.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Datings of key sites will be of use to others working on Quaternary history of Mediterranean islands, and their faunal history</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>695A83E4-FE18-4133-931E-0505B33D6103</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Education,Environment,Culture, Heritage, Museums and Collections</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>http://www.nhm.ac.uk/nature-online/life/dinosaurs-other-extinct-creatures/dwarf-mammoth/index.html?utm_source=mini-mammoth-short-url&amp;utm_medium=mini-mammoth-short-url&amp;utm_campaign=mini-mammoth-short-url</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/92AE6AEC-C5F7-4436-B2FD-4A134239546D"><gtr:id>92AE6AEC-C5F7-4436-B2FD-4A134239546D</gtr:id><gtr:title>New fossil remains of Elephas from the southern Levant: Implications for the evolutionary history of the Asian elephant</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/c047db003343a556ea9b871f846ffaba"><gtr:id>c047db003343a556ea9b871f846ffaba</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Lister A</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/0B255B56-4824-437F-B261-EF09ABB86794"><gtr:id>0B255B56-4824-437F-B261-EF09ABB86794</gtr:i